01:47.758 --> 01:48.993
(man) Norman.

01:51.138 --> 01:53.395
Norman, it's time to get up.

02:23.460 --> 02:25.677
Morning, honey.

02:25.796 --> 02:28.179
You want toast? Here, I'll do this for you.

02:28.298 --> 02:29.347
Thanks.

02:29.466 --> 02:30.765
Get me the butter, will you?

02:30.851 --> 02:32.634
Sure.

02:37.140 --> 02:40.191
- So what's up with Norman?
- What do you mean?

02:40.310 --> 02:41.610
Oh, I just... I walked by his room,

02:41.695 --> 02:43.895
and his bed was made.

02:43.981 --> 02:47.866
Oh, we were talking in my
room, and he fell asleep.

02:47.985 --> 02:50.645
He was just so tired, poor thing.

02:52.539 --> 02:54.239
Don't you think that's weird?

02:54.324 --> 02:56.458
No, I don't think it's weird.

02:56.543 --> 02:57.959
It happens all the time.

02:58.045 --> 02:59.578
We just stay up late.

02:59.663 --> 03:01.329
- What difference does it make?
- Norman's 18.

03:01.465 --> 03:04.445
He shouldn't be sleeping
in the same bed as his mom.

03:06.670 --> 03:08.587
Come on. You're overreacting.

03:08.672 --> 03:10.422
It... He just fell asleep.

03:10.507 --> 03:13.058
It's not a big deal.

03:13.176 --> 03:15.010
- All right, fine.
- Okay.

03:15.145 --> 03:17.072
I hear what you're saying.

03:19.733 --> 03:22.198
- Good.
- Here's your toast.

03:24.271 --> 03:26.187
You headed up to the cabin again?

03:26.273 --> 03:28.940
Yeah, I got a lot to do.

03:29.026 --> 03:32.077
I'm gonna... I'm gonna take
this and eat it in the truck.

03:32.195 --> 03:33.361
I'll see you tonight.

03:33.447 --> 03:36.998
Okay. Okay.

03:37.084 --> 03:38.283
[phone rings]

03:38.368 --> 03:39.668
Be careful.

03:39.753 --> 03:41.753
(Dylan) Bye, Norma.

03:43.457 --> 03:45.006
Hello?

03:45.092 --> 03:48.209
(Ryan) Hi, I'm looking
for Norma Louise Bates.

03:48.295 --> 03:49.711
Who's calling?

03:49.796 --> 03:51.596
This is Ryan Pena from
the law firm of Hart,

03:51.715 --> 03:54.182
Stebbins, and Pena in Boise, Idaho.

03:54.267 --> 03:55.800
This is she.

03:55.886 --> 03:58.847
Miss Bates, we're the
executors of the estate

03:58.909 --> 04:03.141
of Francine Calhoun, your mother.

04:03.226 --> 04:06.528
She died on the 17th, and
my sincere condolences.

04:06.613 --> 04:11.282
We're working here on the
disposition of her estate.

04:18.241 --> 04:21.185
- I'm not interested.
- Pardon?

04:22.546 --> 04:25.714
I'm not interested, but
thank you for calling.

04:37.594 --> 04:40.311
First day of school senior year.

04:40.430 --> 04:41.730
(Norman) It sounds horrible.

04:41.815 --> 04:43.314
I know school always sounds horrible,

04:43.433 --> 04:45.183
but you'll get used to it.

04:45.268 --> 04:47.102
I don't particularly
want to get used to it.

04:47.187 --> 04:48.937
- I liked being home all summer.
- I know.

04:49.022 --> 04:52.857
I liked you being home too,
but you got to go to school.

04:52.943 --> 04:54.242
Besides, it's good for you,

04:54.327 --> 04:56.027
you know, meet new people, try new things?

04:56.113 --> 04:58.803
Oh, by the way, my mother died.

05:00.117 --> 05:01.666
Here's your lunch.

05:01.785 --> 05:04.169
Wait, what are you talking
about, your mother died?

05:04.287 --> 05:05.920
I got a call this morning.

05:06.006 --> 05:09.124
Yep, she's dead,

05:09.209 --> 05:11.710
and I'm only telling you
this because you might need

05:11.795 --> 05:14.629
to know for some legal document some day.

05:14.715 --> 05:17.632
Mother, I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

05:17.718 --> 05:19.350
Do you want me to stay home with you?

05:19.469 --> 05:20.885
No, I'm fine.

05:20.971 --> 05:22.771
Like, I haven't spoken to her in 20 years.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.664
It doesn't mean anything to me.

05:30.864 --> 05:32.981
[engine turns over]

05:48.165 --> 05:49.944
I don't want to go in.

05:51.384 --> 05:53.918
Oh, Norman.

06:00.010 --> 06:03.061
Sweetie, what happened
with you and Miss Watson

06:03.180 --> 06:04.562
is all in the past, okay?

06:04.681 --> 06:06.648
It had nothing to do with you.

06:06.733 --> 06:08.817
No. I can't.

06:08.902 --> 06:11.486
I'm not going.

06:11.571 --> 06:13.855
Norman, stop being dramatic.

06:13.940 --> 06:16.107
Come on, you're just used to being home,

06:16.193 --> 06:18.359
but you got to rip off
that bandage and just go.

06:18.445 --> 06:20.278
I'm not going.

06:28.922 --> 06:30.171
Get out of the car!

06:46.723 --> 06:49.057
Go to school. It's gonna be fine.

06:49.142 --> 06:51.309
I'll see you later.

07:00.120 --> 07:03.571
[dark music]

07:40.493 --> 07:43.455
(Miss Watson) I'll sit with you
while you have your lunch, sweetheart.

07:45.332 --> 07:49.083
I'm so glad you're back, Norman.

07:49.169 --> 07:53.955
This year, we're starting with
the modern poets with TS Elliot.

07:54.040 --> 07:56.257
You'll love him.

07:56.343 --> 08:00.295
"We have lingered in
the chambers of the sea

08:00.380 --> 08:06.801
"with sea girls wreathed
with seaweed red and brown

08:06.887 --> 08:13.024
till human voices wake us and we drown."

08:14.277 --> 08:16.144
Fuck!

08:22.619 --> 08:25.620
[crackling electricity]

08:29.411 --> 08:33.028
- Sync and corrections by madhatters -
- www.addic7ed.com -

08:35.164 --> 08:38.082
It's always beautiful to watch it burn.

08:38.168 --> 08:40.969
How many was that in total?

08:41.054 --> 08:43.304
27.

08:43.390 --> 08:47.892
27 fields burned down, 43 arrests.

08:48.011 --> 08:49.344
Your town's free of this trash now.

08:49.479 --> 08:51.429
You should be a happy man.

09:34.274 --> 09:35.473
Gunner?

09:35.558 --> 09:37.475
Dude.

09:37.560 --> 09:39.394
What are you doing up here?

09:39.479 --> 09:41.029
Remo told me where to find you

09:41.114 --> 09:44.115
before he blew town after
all that DEA crap went down.

09:44.234 --> 09:47.885
He said you rented this land,
told me you could use a hand.

09:49.406 --> 09:50.955
I don't need any help.

09:51.074 --> 09:54.793
He said you'd say that,
but I should come anyway.

09:55.912 --> 09:58.212
We'll see.

10:02.669 --> 10:05.586
Mother! Mother!

10:05.672 --> 10:08.423
- What happened?
- I was at school.

10:08.508 --> 10:11.509
I was eating lunch alone, and then...

10:11.594 --> 10:13.561
Tell me.

10:13.646 --> 10:15.346
And then I felt very strange,

10:15.432 --> 10:18.933
and I thought that Miss Watson
came and sat down next to me

10:19.069 --> 10:20.985
and started talking.

10:30.330 --> 10:31.946
I'm sorry, Mother.

10:36.369 --> 10:38.002
- Do you think you blacked out?
- I don't know.

10:38.121 --> 10:42.090
It didn't feel like it.
It just all felt very real.

10:47.347 --> 10:50.932
I'm sorry.

10:51.017 --> 10:53.801
I ran all the way here.

11:25.718 --> 11:26.717
Hi.

11:26.836 --> 11:28.886
- Hi.
- Hello.

11:29.005 --> 11:30.555
I'm looking for a room for a couple nights.

11:30.673 --> 11:32.140
Do you have anything available?

11:32.225 --> 11:33.445
Yes.

11:36.846 --> 11:38.513
Um, yes, yes, yes, yes.

11:38.598 --> 11:39.564
Of course.

11:39.682 --> 11:41.482
Come on in, please.

11:41.568 --> 11:43.488
Of course.

11:44.771 --> 11:46.404
Let me just get your info.

11:46.523 --> 11:47.772
Uh, what's your name?

11:47.857 --> 11:50.525
- Annika Johnson.
- Okay.

11:50.660 --> 11:54.579
And I'll need to see
an ID and a credit card.

12:15.602 --> 12:17.051
Okay.

12:17.187 --> 12:21.856
I'm gonna put you in room number four.

12:21.941 --> 12:23.357
Here are the keys.

12:23.443 --> 12:26.978
I'm just gonna take him up to the house.

12:27.063 --> 12:29.030
He came home early from school.

12:29.115 --> 12:32.366
He just wasn't feeling very well.

12:32.452 --> 12:35.369
Um, but I'll be back down
later if you need anything.

12:35.455 --> 12:37.288
I usually don't need anything.

12:49.002 --> 12:51.052
Okay, come on.

13:03.333 --> 13:05.833
What you got there?

13:05.919 --> 13:10.054
It's plans for a barn.

13:10.139 --> 13:12.757
For the motel?

13:12.842 --> 13:16.060
No, someplace else.

13:18.598 --> 13:20.064
You joining me for lunch?

13:20.149 --> 13:22.266
No, no, it's just a quick drop-by.

13:22.352 --> 13:27.655
I... I thought we'd continue
our conversation about,

13:27.774 --> 13:30.825
you know, the future of things around here,

13:30.944 --> 13:33.277
and I'm gonna have to take
a more active role, I think.

13:33.363 --> 13:38.833
Sheriff, look, I think I've had my fill

13:38.952 --> 13:44.922
of what it's like to work in
the drug business as a boss.

13:45.024 --> 13:49.343
I mean, I just...

13:49.462 --> 13:52.763
I want to have my own little farm, okay,

13:52.849 --> 13:55.967
and be legal about it

13:56.052 --> 14:00.388
and help people out who
have glaucoma and anxiety.

14:00.473 --> 14:02.139
Thanks.

14:02.225 --> 14:03.608
And...

14:03.693 --> 14:06.527
And just make enough to get by.

14:06.646 --> 14:08.813
Okay? That's...

14:08.898 --> 14:10.698
That's good enough for me,

14:10.817 --> 14:15.983
99 plants legally with a permit.

14:18.041 --> 14:19.323
- I protected you.
- I know.

14:19.409 --> 14:20.958
- I went out of my way for you.
- I know.

14:21.044 --> 14:26.213
No, I really appreciate that.

14:26.332 --> 14:27.715
I do.

14:33.589 --> 14:36.841
Okay, but you know if
we're not working together,

14:36.926 --> 14:38.476
then I can't protect you anymore.

14:38.561 --> 14:40.845
You know that, right?

14:40.930 --> 14:42.428
You'll be on your own.

14:45.234 --> 14:46.600
Yeah, but what I'm doing is legal,

14:46.686 --> 14:49.687
so that shouldn't be a problem, right?

14:49.822 --> 14:53.734
It shouldn't be, but doesn't mean it won't.

14:55.611 --> 14:57.706
All right, I'll see you around, Dylan.

15:07.874 --> 15:09.290
Hey.

15:09.375 --> 15:10.994
Is your mom here?

15:12.428 --> 15:15.846
No, no, she ran to the market.

15:15.932 --> 15:17.298
Can I help you with something?

15:17.383 --> 15:19.575
Ah, it's just my ceiling light's out.

15:20.887 --> 15:22.594
I can take a look at it for you.

15:23.439 --> 15:25.272
All right.

15:29.729 --> 15:32.196
- Excuse me, would you...
- Sure.

15:32.281 --> 15:34.871
Would you hold that
while I change the bulb?

15:37.904 --> 15:40.404
Um...

15:40.490 --> 15:42.990
you and your mom seem very close.

15:43.076 --> 15:45.307
Oh, yes, we are.

15:47.997 --> 15:49.747
But, you know, she does
have a lot on her plate,

15:49.832 --> 15:52.500
and I want to help her, so I...

15:52.585 --> 15:54.227
Your dad's gone?

15:56.089 --> 16:01.759
He died in an accident.

16:03.096 --> 16:04.845
I'm sorry.

16:04.931 --> 16:06.147
That's okay. He, uh...

16:06.265 --> 16:08.482
It wasn't a good situation.

16:08.601 --> 16:10.577
He wasn't a nice man.

16:12.989 --> 16:14.589
Well, maybe he knew my dad.

16:16.609 --> 16:18.423
Your mom's very lucky to have you.

16:20.947 --> 16:24.081
Yeah, well, she's had a lot of bad breaks,

16:24.167 --> 16:26.033
even moving here to start over,

16:26.119 --> 16:27.835
and let me tell you, a
lot of people around here

16:27.954 --> 16:29.370
have not been very nice to her.

16:29.455 --> 16:31.088
And now they're putting this new road in,

16:31.174 --> 16:32.957
and we're afraid it's
gonna wreck our business.

16:33.042 --> 16:34.125
That sucks.

16:34.210 --> 16:35.543
Yeah, it sucks. It's...

16:35.628 --> 16:37.294
Sorry, I shouldn't be complaining.

16:37.380 --> 16:38.846
I shouldn't be telling you any of this.

16:38.965 --> 16:41.932
No, no, that's okay. It's okay.

16:42.018 --> 16:42.933
There.

16:43.019 --> 16:45.719
[chuckles]

16:48.141 --> 16:50.558
So why are you visiting us?

16:50.643 --> 16:52.693
Work or...

16:52.812 --> 16:59.233
Well, I could give you the fake story

16:59.318 --> 17:00.985
or tell you the truth.

17:01.120 --> 17:04.821
You've been so honest with me.

17:10.329 --> 17:12.135
I work at parties.

17:13.715 --> 17:15.465
What kind of parties?

17:17.050 --> 17:20.838
Big, expensive parties with
a lot of wealthy men at them.

17:24.393 --> 17:27.011
Oh.

17:27.096 --> 17:28.929
Should I not have told you that?

17:29.015 --> 17:32.566
No, no. It's fine.

17:32.685 --> 17:37.238
I-I understand. I'm glad you did.

17:46.866 --> 17:48.700
You seem like a nice girl.

17:50.703 --> 17:52.586
I am.

17:52.705 --> 17:54.172
Thank you for saying that.

18:03.182 --> 18:07.935
♪ Are you mine? ♪

18:08.054 --> 18:12.690
♪ Are you mine? All right ♪

18:12.775 --> 18:15.693
[rock music playing]

18:18.114 --> 18:21.732
♪ I guess what I'm trying to
say is I need the deep end ♪

18:24.570 --> 18:27.404
[eerie music]

19:01.023 --> 19:02.606
(Dylan) Get out of the car!

19:10.700 --> 19:12.533
It's me.

19:24.463 --> 19:26.680
- What do you want?
- I just...

19:26.799 --> 19:27.825
Stay there.

19:30.853 --> 19:33.804
Look, I followed you up
here so I could talk to you.

19:33.889 --> 19:35.556
I didn't want to go to the motel 'cause

19:35.641 --> 19:36.979
I knew you wouldn't want that.

19:38.978 --> 19:41.362
Talk about what?

19:41.480 --> 19:43.538
I just wanted to give you something.

19:44.984 --> 19:47.534
My mom... she died,

19:47.653 --> 19:50.321
and there's some cash
from the sale of the house,

19:50.456 --> 19:52.101
and I wanted you to have it.

19:55.878 --> 19:57.161
- I don't want it.
- Dylan.

19:57.246 --> 19:59.129
I don't want it!

19:59.215 --> 20:01.626
Get back in the van,
turn around, and leave.

20:02.835 --> 20:04.628
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

20:07.006 --> 20:09.673
Leave.

20:09.759 --> 20:11.592
Okay.

20:47.141 --> 20:49.558
I've been thinking about something.

20:49.677 --> 20:50.833
What is it?

20:52.763 --> 20:54.925
I don't think you need to go to school.

20:56.100 --> 20:57.238
I don't?

20:59.186 --> 21:02.571
Well, I mean, you need to
get your high school diploma,

21:02.690 --> 21:07.192
but I looked into it,
and you could homeschool.

21:07.328 --> 21:09.037
You'd be okay with that?

21:10.781 --> 21:12.614
I think so.

21:12.700 --> 21:15.701
I mean, I don't think
school's been good for you,

21:15.786 --> 21:18.203
and it's also a little selfish on my part.

21:18.339 --> 21:20.922
I want to take a business
class at the community college,

21:21.041 --> 21:22.124
self-marketing.

21:22.209 --> 21:23.425
You know, we have to be proactive

21:23.544 --> 21:24.876
about this bypass happening.

21:24.962 --> 21:27.879
We can't just sit by and lose our business,

21:27.965 --> 21:30.682
and so I thought

21:30.768 --> 21:34.122
maybe it's time that
I gave you a promotion.

21:36.190 --> 21:38.223
A promotion?

21:38.359 --> 21:41.643
I'm gonna make you motel manager.

21:41.729 --> 21:44.062
- No.
- Yeah.

21:44.198 --> 21:46.481
- Yeah.
- Hotel manager?

21:46.567 --> 21:48.900
Yeah, you would be in charge of everything.

21:48.986 --> 21:50.652
You'd run the motel.

21:50.738 --> 21:53.405
What do you think?

21:53.457 --> 21:56.992
All right, mother, I'll be motel manager.

22:06.220 --> 22:08.754
I'm gonna go to sleep now...

22:08.839 --> 22:10.172
Okay.

22:10.257 --> 22:12.924
But I think you should go to your bed.

22:13.010 --> 22:14.593
I should?

22:14.645 --> 22:15.761
I-I can.

22:15.896 --> 22:17.733
I do it all the time, but...

22:19.183 --> 22:22.190
Well, it's just that
Dylan said something to me

22:23.771 --> 22:26.655
that it's not good for you to be sleeping

22:26.774 --> 22:30.108
in my bed or on my bed,
like, sleeping in here.

22:30.244 --> 22:31.827
What's Dylan got to do with us?

22:31.945 --> 22:34.162
Well, he's a man, and I'm just your mother.

22:34.281 --> 22:35.697
I don't always know what's good for you

22:35.783 --> 22:38.366
in a manly kind of a way.

22:38.452 --> 22:41.536
I mean, you are 18 years old.

22:41.622 --> 22:44.456
So you don't want me
sleeping in here anymore?

22:44.591 --> 22:46.291
No, it's not that I don't want it...

22:46.376 --> 22:49.878
No, no, you just don't
think it's good for me.

22:49.963 --> 22:51.797
Maybe not.

22:56.603 --> 22:57.926
- Okay.
- Okay.

23:00.557 --> 23:01.928
Goodnight then, mother.

23:06.230 --> 23:07.946
I love you, Norman.

23:08.031 --> 23:09.865
I know.

23:26.333 --> 23:30.585
Shit. Damn it.

23:38.846 --> 23:41.229
I thought you left.

23:41.348 --> 23:42.681
Yeah, well, where was

23:42.733 --> 23:44.349
I supposed to go in
the middle of the night?

23:44.434 --> 23:47.068
I drove a couple miles down
the road and bedded down.

23:47.187 --> 23:49.404
And now it's day, and you're still here.

23:49.523 --> 23:50.856
Yeah, well, this morning, old Millie

23:50.991 --> 23:52.407
wasn't feeling too good.

23:52.526 --> 23:56.244
She started but overheated
after a couple of miles.

23:56.363 --> 23:58.363
Hey, you got a spare radiator hose?

23:58.499 --> 23:59.865
On me?

23:59.917 --> 24:01.700
On my person? No.

24:01.752 --> 24:03.201
Yeah, well, don't worry about it.

24:03.287 --> 24:05.120
I'm sure you got stuff to do.

24:05.205 --> 24:07.672
Nothing more important than
making sure you get out of town.

24:07.758 --> 24:10.663
How far a walk is it to the
nearest auto parts store?

24:13.380 --> 24:15.213
It's a ways.

24:19.136 --> 24:20.936
Can I get a ride?

24:26.810 --> 24:29.561
All right.

24:29.646 --> 24:31.513
Thanks, man.

24:33.317 --> 24:36.151
Did you know I owned Millie,
my van, three different times?

24:36.236 --> 24:37.903
The last time I thought I sold it for good,

24:37.955 --> 24:40.322
but when I got back from
Costa Rica, my buddy, Tom...

24:40.407 --> 24:41.904
I don't want to make small talk.

24:43.710 --> 24:45.961
Look, you don't have to be so angry.

24:46.079 --> 24:47.863
What were you expecting?

24:49.510 --> 24:51.550
I don't know what I was expecting.

24:51.585 --> 24:53.468
It's just...

25:01.511 --> 25:02.928
It was a bad idea coming here.

25:02.980 --> 25:04.295
I'm full of them.

25:06.984 --> 25:11.686
Now that my mother's gone,
I don't have any more family.

25:11.772 --> 25:13.488
That's a strange feeling.

25:19.279 --> 25:20.695
Look, before I leave, I just...

25:20.781 --> 25:23.338
I had one thing I wanted to say.

25:24.534 --> 25:25.796
What's that?

25:27.537 --> 25:28.911
I know I'm your dad.

25:34.378 --> 25:37.212
I thought so much about
it since I was here.

25:37.297 --> 25:38.880
That's why Norma ran away from home

25:38.966 --> 25:40.548
and married that kid from high school.

25:40.634 --> 25:42.350
I now know that's what must've happened.

25:42.469 --> 25:44.052
- I don't care.
- Look, do you know my mother?

25:44.137 --> 25:45.520
She was crazy.

25:45.639 --> 25:48.473
I mean, she was literally crazy.

25:48.558 --> 25:50.225
And my dad, our dad,

25:50.310 --> 25:52.944
he was the most violent
man I've ever known.

25:53.030 --> 25:57.352
There was no place safe
for us, for me and Norma,

26:00.821 --> 26:04.656
except with each other.

26:15.385 --> 26:17.496
I'm taking you back to your van.

26:31.935 --> 26:33.184
Sheriff.

26:33.236 --> 26:34.850
Off duty, huh?

26:39.359 --> 26:41.526
What can I do for you?

26:41.611 --> 26:44.112
We both just lost our jobs.

26:44.197 --> 26:46.197
Yeah, what with the DEA coming over here

26:46.249 --> 26:49.534
and burning up all the fields.

26:49.619 --> 26:51.536
Yeah, well, at least you're not in jail.

26:51.621 --> 26:53.254
That supposed to be funny?

26:53.373 --> 26:55.040
My understanding was that you were supposed

26:55.125 --> 26:56.458
to be protecting us.

26:56.543 --> 26:58.157
And this town.

27:00.180 --> 27:01.796
All right, let me get this straight.

27:01.882 --> 27:03.765
So you both worked in the drug business,

27:03.884 --> 27:05.800
and now you're shocked
that the DEA showed up?

27:05.886 --> 27:08.937
This town's been growing
weed for nearly 40 years.

27:09.056 --> 27:10.605
You screwed up.

27:10.724 --> 27:12.640
You screwed it up for everybody.

27:12.726 --> 27:15.226
I hope they run your ass out of town.

27:15.278 --> 27:17.046
I wish you weren't a cop.

27:18.693 --> 27:21.116
If I wasn't a cop, what?

27:21.201 --> 27:22.650
I'd kick your ass, you piece of...

27:53.129 --> 27:56.296
Hey, Emma. You're not busy, are you?

27:56.415 --> 27:59.383
I have something I need to tell you.

27:59.468 --> 28:01.051
Everything okay, Norman?

28:01.137 --> 28:02.986
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

28:03.088 --> 28:04.588
I just... You should know

28:04.673 --> 28:06.807
I'm not coming back to school this year.

28:06.926 --> 28:08.142
Mother's letting me homeschool.

28:08.260 --> 28:10.761
She needs help around the motel.

28:10.896 --> 28:13.063
I've been made manager.

28:15.601 --> 28:16.722
Oh.

28:21.824 --> 28:24.992
Actually, there's something
I need to tell you too.

28:25.110 --> 28:28.111
I got some bad news at the doctor.

28:28.197 --> 28:30.080
Are you okay?

28:30.166 --> 28:33.576
My lung capacity has
diminished, like, a lot,

28:36.672 --> 28:39.540
and that's not the reason
why I'm telling you, I just...

28:39.625 --> 28:41.816
I hate to hear that you
won't be at school anymore.

28:43.546 --> 28:45.006
I'm sorry, Emma.

28:47.550 --> 28:49.216
I wish I could leave school.

28:53.389 --> 28:56.773
Well, why can't you?

28:56.859 --> 28:58.725
We could study together here.

29:02.731 --> 29:04.865
Would that be weird if I homeschooled too?

29:04.984 --> 29:07.201
I don't want you to think I'm,
like, copying you or anything.

29:07.319 --> 29:09.703
No, I'd like it.

29:09.822 --> 29:12.206
You were the only reason
I liked school anyway.

29:16.545 --> 29:18.212
This is so great.

29:18.330 --> 29:19.880
I mean, if these are my best years,

29:19.999 --> 29:21.484
I want to spend them with you

29:24.253 --> 29:26.303
and your mom and Dylan.

29:27.923 --> 29:29.556
I think we should date.

29:33.596 --> 29:35.312
What?

29:41.604 --> 29:43.272
Will you go out with me, Emma?

29:45.774 --> 29:47.908
Are you saying this
because you think I'm dying?

29:48.027 --> 29:49.576
- It's not imminent.
- No, that's not why.

29:49.695 --> 29:53.196
It's just time.

30:00.422 --> 30:02.823
- Really?
- Really.

30:04.432 --> 30:06.760
Don't you think?

30:06.879 --> 30:09.129
It's been time for a while.

30:28.734 --> 30:30.067
Hi, Norma.

30:30.152 --> 30:32.402
Hi, Dylan. Sit down.

30:32.488 --> 30:34.821
I got to talk to you.

30:55.311 --> 30:57.177
Your grandmother died.

31:05.938 --> 31:08.905
I'm sorry, Norma.

31:08.991 --> 31:11.108
I guess it won't make a
difference about anything,

31:11.193 --> 31:15.362
but I don't know, I just
thought you should know.

31:17.499 --> 31:19.282
You okay?

31:33.932 --> 31:35.932
It's her hair ribbon.

31:40.973 --> 31:42.723
She used to...

31:42.808 --> 31:44.191
She used to tell me how she wore it

31:44.309 --> 31:48.163
to a dance in high
school with a blue dress.

31:50.032 --> 31:52.282
You know that's the
only memory I have of her

31:52.368 --> 31:53.689
where she sounded happy?

31:56.655 --> 31:58.352
She gave it to me when I was little,

31:59.998 --> 32:05.462
and I-I always kept it.

32:05.547 --> 32:11.001
I-I always hoped that she
would be that person again.

32:13.889 --> 32:16.171
What was wrong with her
that she wasn't happy?

32:19.762 --> 32:22.430
I don't know. She just wasn't healthy.

32:24.638 --> 32:28.351
It was something that was never discussed.

32:28.437 --> 32:31.855
She... She took a lot of pills.

32:31.940 --> 32:34.741
I didn't even know where she got them,

32:34.860 --> 32:36.943
and she was sedated a lot.

32:57.633 --> 32:59.182
[metal, glass clanks]

33:04.306 --> 33:05.972
Hey!

33:06.058 --> 33:07.607
Psst! Get out of here!

33:07.726 --> 33:10.060
Hey.

33:19.788 --> 33:22.789
[water rushing]

33:34.052 --> 33:35.469
[water drips]

33:40.092 --> 33:42.976
[dark music]

33:54.523 --> 33:57.524
[water pattering]

34:30.309 --> 34:32.108
Norman!

34:32.194 --> 34:33.944
Get in the house!

34:41.737 --> 34:44.571
What the hell were you thinking?

34:44.656 --> 34:46.822
You can't do stuff like this, Norman.

34:46.909 --> 34:48.742
You are the motel manager now.

34:48.827 --> 34:50.293
You can't be skulking around the dark,

34:50.379 --> 34:51.795
peering into the guests' bathrooms.

34:51.880 --> 34:54.797
It's not normal!

34:54.882 --> 34:57.083
You're right.

34:57.169 --> 35:00.220
I'm so sorry, Mother. It
won't ever happen again.

35:11.733 --> 35:14.734
[Norma crying]

35:21.693 --> 35:25.195
Mother. Mother.

35:25.280 --> 35:26.947
Mother, I'm sorry.

35:27.032 --> 35:28.531
I'm so sorry.

35:28.617 --> 35:30.834
I was just picking up trash
that some raccoon got into,

35:30.919 --> 35:32.118
and I saw her through the window.

35:32.204 --> 35:33.670
I didn't mean anything.

35:33.755 --> 35:35.171
I know it was wrong of me,

35:35.257 --> 35:37.707
but it's nothing more
than what it looked like.

35:37.793 --> 35:39.593
I'm not crying because of that.

35:39.711 --> 35:43.713
I'm crying because my mother's dead.

35:43.799 --> 35:46.800
[crying]

35:52.891 --> 35:54.057
It's stupid.

35:54.142 --> 35:56.026
I didn't even really know her.

35:59.314 --> 36:03.900
I think that I am just grieving
because I never had a mother.

36:09.157 --> 36:10.424
And now you're growing up.

36:12.210 --> 36:16.796
Maybe growing up, but I'm
not going anywhere, okay?

36:16.915 --> 36:19.082
You know that, Mother.

36:19.217 --> 36:22.886
- I love you.
- I love you too.

36:30.178 --> 36:32.262
I'm gonna slide over a bit.

36:32.347 --> 36:33.454
Why?

36:35.363 --> 36:39.030
I just thought you were gonna
lay down just for a minute.

36:41.189 --> 36:44.295
Oh, well, I thought we
weren't doing that anymore.

36:47.446 --> 36:52.823
Just for tonight, because I'm so sad.

36:54.369 --> 36:56.870
Move over, you silly woman.

37:09.101 --> 37:11.134
[sighs]

37:28.287 --> 37:29.836
Hey, dude.

37:29.922 --> 37:32.122
Hey, did you know your uncle
knows all about construction?

37:32.207 --> 37:33.707
No, I didn't.

37:33.792 --> 37:38.178
He's built houses and a
couple barns in Costa Rica.

37:38.263 --> 37:40.464
How lucky is that?

37:40.549 --> 37:42.682
- You were leaving.
- Yeah, that's true.

37:42.768 --> 37:45.936
But the van... It wasn't the rad hose.

37:46.055 --> 37:47.854
It needs another part.

37:47.940 --> 37:51.274
They ordered it for me, so
it should be here tomorrow

37:51.393 --> 37:53.182
or the day after, latest.

37:55.230 --> 37:57.212
So you decided to drive back up here?

37:59.401 --> 38:01.735
(Dylan) That's bullshit.

38:01.820 --> 38:04.037
Whoa.

38:04.123 --> 38:05.455
Take a walk, Gunner.

38:05.574 --> 38:06.873
All right.

38:15.134 --> 38:17.050
How do you expect me to
have a relationship with you

38:17.136 --> 38:18.599
under the circumstances?

38:20.422 --> 38:22.413
Norma never has to know I'm here.

38:23.842 --> 38:26.426
Please.

38:26.512 --> 38:27.695
You're my son.

38:29.815 --> 38:31.749
Just let me be with you a little while.

38:34.103 --> 38:36.956
I won't ever ask you
for anything beyond that.

38:48.117 --> 38:51.868
(Emma) It looks like we can
take all the same classes.

38:51.954 --> 38:53.420
We have a quiz in English next week.

38:53.505 --> 38:54.921
We better get started.

38:55.007 --> 38:57.124
I'm excited. This is gonna be fun.

38:57.209 --> 38:58.788
It's very empowering.

39:01.130 --> 39:03.680
So, uh...

39:03.799 --> 39:05.966
So how are we gonna do this?

39:06.051 --> 39:07.767
Homeschooling? We're just gonna sit here...

39:07.853 --> 39:09.425
No, dating.

39:11.557 --> 39:14.736
Well, I guess we're just
gonna go places together

39:16.979 --> 39:18.945
like a normal date.

39:19.031 --> 39:23.650
Yeah. I've never been on a date.

39:23.735 --> 39:24.898
Never?

39:26.872 --> 39:29.372
What about Bradley?

39:29.491 --> 39:32.492
We never... We never dated.

39:32.578 --> 39:35.336
You know, that's, uh... yeah,
that was something different.

39:37.332 --> 39:40.300
Well, if you accomplished
all that without dating,

39:40.385 --> 39:41.942
and may she rest with God,

39:44.756 --> 39:46.520
then you should do just fine on a date.

39:49.082 --> 39:50.242
(Annika) Hello?

39:52.681 --> 39:54.386
Hi, may I help you?

39:56.401 --> 39:57.984
- Um...
- Oh, Emma, this is...

39:58.070 --> 40:00.770
This is Annika, room four.

40:00.856 --> 40:03.440
Nice to meet you. That's a beautiful dress.

40:03.525 --> 40:04.858
Thank you.

40:04.943 --> 40:06.243
I'm wondering, could you tell me

40:06.361 --> 40:08.078
where a restaurant called
Olive and Anchor is?

40:08.197 --> 40:09.996
I looked it up online, but I can't quite

40:10.082 --> 40:11.448
figure out how to get there.

40:11.533 --> 40:13.083
It's in the village. It's very nice.

40:13.202 --> 40:15.335
Yeah, but it's a little bit hidden.

40:15.420 --> 40:16.870
It's down one of the side streets.

40:16.955 --> 40:19.456
It's, uh...

40:19.541 --> 40:21.541
Well, actually I, uh...

40:21.627 --> 40:23.093
I have to go into town anyway

40:23.212 --> 40:26.680
to pick up that new
thermostat for room seven.

40:26.765 --> 40:29.549
So, um, I was gonna walk,

40:29.635 --> 40:32.686
but why don't I drive with
you and show you where it is,

40:32.771 --> 40:34.187
and then I can walk home.

40:34.273 --> 40:35.639
That's very nice of you, Norman.

40:35.724 --> 40:37.691
How can I say no to that?

40:37.776 --> 40:38.725
You can go now?

40:38.810 --> 40:41.228
Yeah. I'm the manager.

40:41.313 --> 40:45.865
Um, I'll be back in an hour or so.

40:48.070 --> 40:49.402
It was nice to meet you.

40:49.488 --> 40:51.454
Shall we?

41:02.834 --> 41:06.317
So you're working? Is
that where you're going?

41:08.423 --> 41:09.883
It's a kind of work.

41:12.477 --> 41:14.326
Why do you do this kind of work?

41:17.482 --> 41:19.498
You know how your mom takes care of you?

41:20.652 --> 41:22.686
I didn't have that luxury,

41:22.771 --> 41:25.939
so I'm doing this to get some money saved

41:26.074 --> 41:27.801
and make a living, that's all.

41:30.862 --> 41:32.579
I'm sorry.

41:32.664 --> 41:35.448
Don't be. I'm fine.

41:35.534 --> 41:39.071
It's just people... People's bodies.

41:40.872 --> 41:42.589
Once you start touching somebody's body,

41:42.674 --> 41:45.125
the rest of it just kind of melts away,

41:45.210 --> 41:49.809
and then you're just there, two bodies.

41:51.800 --> 41:53.739
Sometimes it even feels good.

41:56.188 --> 41:59.105
It's just sex. Sex is sex.

41:59.191 --> 42:01.057
We all need it.

42:04.229 --> 42:07.814
♪ Guess I feel for your greatest line ♪

42:07.899 --> 42:09.816
Do I turn up here?

42:09.901 --> 42:12.402
Not... Not here, no.

42:12.487 --> 42:14.321
Not yet.

42:14.456 --> 42:16.478
Turn down that road up ahead.

43:18.970 --> 43:21.888
[dark music]

43:34.202 --> 43:35.618
[car alarm beeps]

